The Kebbi State Police Command has confirmed the abduction of an 18-year-old girl at Gangaren NEPA, Birnin Kebbi, in the early hours of Friday morning. DSP Nafi’u Abubakar, the Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO) of the Command who confirmed the development to the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) said the police were on top of the situation, as all efforts were already in place to rescue the victim. Abubakar advised the public to furnish the police with useful information on the matter. He also urged the public to report to security agencies any suspicious move to enable it take the necessary action to foil the illicit act. NAN reports that the father of the kidnapped lady, Faruq Mohammed is a member of the Nigerian Security and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC), Kebbi State Command. Speaking in an interview with newsmen, Mohammed said the gunmen came into the area and started operation. “When they came to my house, I noticed some noise and understood that something was wrong. I have two exits in my house. “I decided that we should go out through the garage, unfortunately, on opening the door, we met one of the bandits fully armed by the side of my car, we had to find another route and jumped into the neighbouring house. “The bandits broke into my house and started searching from room to room, unfortunately, my daughter was sleeping in her room, when they knocked, she opened the room and they picked her up.”